sub_title: Adviser to the clerk of the council / Community liaison officer
summary:
I am a broker between technology, society and politics. During my internship in Indonesia, I saw the influence of social, cultural and religious aspects on the progress of a technical project. This was one of the reasons to study Cultural Anthropology. A master's degree focused on development work resulted in jobs in Bhutan and Cambodia. Back in the Netherlands, my knowledge of and experience with “Community development” and “people’s participation” also proved applicable in Dutch society. From a strong democratic awareness, I still enjoy working with resident groups, local government and colleagues on new projects and renewal of local democratic decision-making.
After my studies I entered the world with a lot of theoretical knowledge. Now, 30 years later, I would like to share all that knowledge and experience with others in the world.
